args: Noelle, I am assigning you the task of\nlooking into the Commander's current\nsituation and whereabouts.
In truth, the story you were told about him\nabandoning our country was just a cover.
You're aware of the former Kingdom of\nAlberia in southern Grastaea, yes?
Ever since they changed their name\nto the Dyrenell Empire, the country\nhas become deeply unstable.
And so, the Commander took on a\nfalse identity as a mercenary and\nentered the country to learn more.
He is acting under royal decree.
After forming a band of mercenaries, he\nhad been working to establish himself in\nthe Empire in order to gain their trust.
All of this was good news, and our agents\nhad been keeping us apprised of any\nnew developments. However...
Yesterday, we received word that his\nmercenary force was wiped out.
But as the Commander was acting under\nroyal decree, we must learn the truth.
Hence, you are to make contact with our\nagents in the Empire and conduct an\ninvestigation.
Um...could you maybe share what\nyou know about the Shadewolves?
Everything I know was in my report,\nso don't bother asking me how they\nmanaged to get slaughtered.
Not the battle, but the aftermath.\nI'm gonna be having nightmares\nabout that for the rest of my life...
Didn't see him, but then again,\nit was quite the mess.
Even if he did manage to escape,\nit doesn't mean he's still alive.
Still, I've heard a rumor about a man\nwho's been going around recently\nhunting down imperial soldiers.
And not just them—apparently more than\none innocent person has gotten caught\nup in the crossfire.
You ask me, the Shadewolves' leader is\nstill alive—and thirsty for vengeance.
And you think that man is...\nthe Commander?
Like I said, it's just a theory.

But imperial soldiers ARE being attacked—
that much is certain. Hell, I heard tale of
an entire village that got wiped out when
someone poisoned the well.
If you're curious, you might try asking\nsome of the other agents. Doubtless\nthey've heard rumors I haven't.
Th-these are your orders from HQ.
Thank you. Please take my report back\nto them as soon as you can.
You want to hear what I know about the\n＂Shadewolves' leader,＂ yes?
Well, take this for what it's worth,\nwhich may be nothing.

Rumor has it that a hooded man has been
going around murdering anyone who has
given aid to the imperials—even if they
had little choice in the matter.
He sets entire towns to blaze even if\nimperial soldiers only passed through,\nand kills any who try to escape.
I can only assume that he's afraid\nof his identity being discovered.
Although given that all the rumors are\ncalling him ＂the Shadewolves' leader,＂\nit seems a bit late for caution.
So maybe he's just pissed off and\nwants to see the world burn.
Hell, I've even heard rumors of him\nroaming the countryside at night with\na bloody sword in his hand.
What could drive someone to that...?
I don't know—but even assuming the\nstories are exaggerated, this is a\nheadache the world doesn't need.
Oh, but if you want to know more,\ntalk to my friend in the town east of here.
A'yup. We had us a report of someone\nwhat looked just like the Commander.
Can't promise it's him, now.\nJust repeatin' what I heard.
That's fine. I'll go see for myself.
In that case, you wanna make your way\nto the Halidom—a castle deep inside the\nMistholt.
Apparently he's joined up with the seventh\nheir to Alberia, the prince what's fightin'\nthe Empire.
I may have finally found him...
Er, thank you. I'll go back to HQ\nand let them know at once!
...So it's true, then.\nThe Shadewolves are no more.
Though it appears the only way to find out\nHOW is to ask the Commander himself.
You heard he had joined up with Alberia's\nseventh scion, correct?
Yes, but I...um...wasn't able to\nconfirm it myself.
It makes sense. In fact, it is consistent\nwith why he was originally sent to Alberia.
The Commander's true mission was\nto learn the secrets of the Alberian\nroyal family's dragonblood.
I will write down new orders for him.\nYou are to deliver them at once.
I'm not a commander anymore.\nJust a mercenary.
I assume you're looking into the rumors\nof the ＂Shadewolves' leader＂?
And yet, you have not come all this way\njust to verify the veracity of such rumors,\nnow have you?
What do you want of me? ...No, I suppose\nthat's a foolish question for a messenger.\nYou bring new orders, I take it?
...Hmph. So they want me to capture the\nprince and drag him home, do they?
Y-you just tore up your orders!
Go home, little messenger. Go home and\ntell them that I will carry out this mission\nin my own way.
The choice of capturing—or killing—this\nprince will be made by me alone.
Glad I was around to hear that.
Ranzal? What are you doing here?
We caught word that someone was\nskulking about outside, so we decided\nto strengthen our patrols.
Ah. I see you have all come, then.
I think we deserve an explanation, Victor.
Stand down, Noelle. With them, it's safer\nto show no readiness to fight.
...After holding me back, the Commander\ntold everyone the truth about what\nbrought him to their door.
Shockingly, the prince didn't seem fazed\nby the fact that he was a spy at all.
In fact, he even invited him to join them\nas an ally at their castle!
They spared my life as well.
They set me free at the edge of their\nterritory and told me to go home.
